## SwiftPM Dependencies

The public Swift packages reference `swift-cgit2` through SwiftPM. It is a
package dependency, not a vendored source checkout in the publishable tree.

PhotoSorter can optionally reference `mlx-swift`, `mlx-swift-examples`, and
`swift-transformers` through SwiftPM when `PHOTOSORTER_ENABLE_LOCAL_FASTVLM=1`
and local FastVLM sources are present. Those optional checkouts and model
artifacts are not part of the default publishable tree.

## Build-Time CPython For iOS Examples

The source tree does not vendor BeeWare Python-Apple-support or CPython
framework binaries. The checked-in iOS example build phases can populate a local
BeeWare CPython iOS cache and embed `Python.framework` plus the Python home into
developer-built app bundles.

That is acceptable for source release because the generated frameworks and
stdlib are local build outputs. Any public binary app distribution that includes
those embedded runtime files must carry the applicable BeeWare, CPython, and
Python Software Foundation notices/licenses for the exact runtime bundle being
distributed.

## PhotoSorter FastVLM Local Inputs

PhotoSorter local FastVLM Swift source, MLX checkouts, and FastVLM model bundles
are opt-in local development inputs. They live under ignored paths such as
`Examples/iOS/PhotoSorter/Local/FastVLM/`,
`Examples/iOS/PhotoSorter/Vendor/mlx-swift*`, and
`Examples/iOS/PhotoSorter/Resources/FastVLM/model/`.

Those files must not be included in the default source release unless their
upstream license terms, model terms, and notices have been reviewed and added to
this notice set.
